    <string name="https_filtering_explain_title">How does this work?</string>
    <string name="https_filtering_explain_body">HTTPS Filtering intercepts web traffic from your selected browsers and injects a script to block annoying popups, pop-unders, and redirect ads.\n\nTo do this, a local Root CA certificate must be installed on your device. This certificate is generated locally and never leaves your phone. Banking apps, Google, and other sensitive services are never intercepted.</string>
    <string name="https_filtering_ca_title">Root CA Certificate</string>
    <string name="https_filtering_ca_desc">To block popups on HTTPS sites, install the BlockAds Root CA certificate on your device. Follow the steps below.</string>
    <string name="https_filtering_export_ca">Step 1: Save Certificate to Downloads</string>
    <string name="https_filtering_cert_saved">Certificate saved to Downloads!</string>
    <string name="https_filtering_install_steps">Step 2: Install the certificate manually:\n\n1. Go to Settings → Security → Encryption &amp; credentials\n2. Tap \"Install a certificate\" → \"CA certificate\"\n3. Select \"BlockAds-RootCA.crt\" from Downloads\n4. Confirm the installation</string>
